Now is the time to prove
that thou art mighty.

684
01:13:40,479 --> 01:13:44,720
Muhammad also prayed (peace
and blessings be upon him ).

685
01:13:45,158 --> 01:13:50,399
God, revealer of the Book,
caller to account.

686
01:13:51,238 --> 01:13:56,118
Whatever the power it is the
protects Muhammad, overcome it.

687
01:13:56,238 --> 01:13:59,158
Turn the confederates to flight.

688
01:13:59,319 --> 01:14:05,640
And show these muslims once and
for all thy power reign supreme.

689
01:14:05,960 --> 01:14:10,000
Turn them to flight and
cause them to quake.

690
01:15:04,520 --> 01:15:07,238
Men of Arabia!

691
01:15:41,238 --> 01:15:45,238
Hold your ground, it will pass.
Hold your ground!

692
01:16:38,439 --> 01:16:40,880
Back to Mecca.

693
01:16:48,118 --> 01:16:51,038
God has saved us.

694
01:16:55,279 --> 01:16:59,800
One day, The Prophet (peace and
blessings be upon him ) looked at us...

695
01:16:59,960 --> 01:17:05,600
...and said: '' l dreamed that l enter the
Kaaba with it's key in my hand. ''

696
01:17:18,399 --> 01:17:22,038
We shall journey to Mecca
for the pilgrimage...

697
01:17:22,198 --> 01:17:25,479
...and worship at
the holly Kaaba.

698
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:29,000
He's coming here?
Without weapons?

699
01:17:29,158 --> 01:17:31,840
He knows we can't crash
our peacefull pilgrimage.

700
01:17:32,000 --> 01:17:34,319
All of Arabia will
rise up against us.

701
01:17:34,439 --> 01:17:37,198
Blast him!
Blast Muhammad!

702
01:17:37,319 --> 01:17:40,960
There is nothing we can do.
Let them in.

703
01:17:41,078 --> 01:17:45,479
What? Bear the shame of
let in Muhammad worship in Mecca.

704
01:17:45,600 --> 01:17:48,880
lt's over. lt's over.

705
01:17:49,038 --> 01:17:53,038
l am sending Suhayl. l will
let him promise the world.

706
01:17:53,158 --> 01:17:55,920
But the muslims
will not enter Mecca.

707
01:18:00,720 --> 01:18:06,600
We suggest a compromise.
A peace treaty.

708
01:18:07,198 --> 01:18:12,680
We promise not to attack any of your
people and you'll promise the same.

709
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:14,600
For ten years.

710
01:18:14,720 --> 01:18:18,198
We will be allowed to enter Mecca,
worship at the Kaaba?

711
01:18:18,319 --> 01:18:21,118
Most definitely.

712
01:18:21,238 --> 01:18:25,038
Starting next year.

713
01:18:25,560 --> 01:18:28,238
You came back without
even entering Mecca?

714
01:18:28,359 --> 01:18:32,399
But we will next year.
- And every year after that.

715
01:18:32,520 --> 01:18:37,760
For ten years.
- For three days at a a time.

716
01:18:38,399 --> 01:18:43,000
Do have ten years of peace.
Ten years.

717
01:18:43,158 --> 01:18:48,920
Yes. The message of Islam
can travel far in ten years.

718
01:19:08,000 --> 01:19:10,920
Amr?
- Why are you going to Medina?

719
01:19:11,038 --> 01:19:13,880
To see Muhammad.

720
01:19:14,000 --> 01:19:19,078
For what reason?
What reason!

721
01:19:19,198 --> 01:19:22,359
To become a muslim.

722
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:26,840
l thought you were coming to kill him.
- You ment to defend him?

723
01:19:26,960 --> 01:19:33,000
How can we deny it any longer?
He is God's Prophet.

724
01:19:35,640 --> 01:19:41,238
l bare witness that there
is no god but God...

725
01:19:41,840 --> 01:19:44,439
...and you are
his Messenger.

726
01:19:45,960 --> 01:19:52,158
And l bare witness that there
is no god but Allah...

727
01:19:52,680 --> 01:19:57,720
...and you Muhammad
are his Messenger.

728
01:20:50,479 --> 01:20:53,279
Many muslims
have been killed.

729
01:20:53,479 --> 01:20:56,319
They have broken the treaty.

730
01:20:58,038 --> 01:21:02,439
The Prophet (peace and
blessings be upon him ) decided,...

731
01:21:02,680 --> 01:21:08,840
'' lt's time to return to Mecca.''
- Yes Messenger of God.

732
01:21:29,880 --> 01:21:35,000
We are ready Messenger of God.
-On to Mecca!

733
01:21:42,520 --> 01:21:48,920
Now they are the army of 10000 with
our greatest leader is at their head.

734
01:22:06,479 --> 01:22:10,279
Hold! Stop where you are!
-l've come to speak with Muhammad.

735
01:22:11,038 --> 01:22:13,319
Show your hands.

736
01:22:13,439 --> 01:22:17,158
No! lt would be foolish of
me to trying hurt him now.

737
01:22:17,319 --> 01:22:20,560
That never stopped you before.
- l come in peace.

738
01:22:20,720 --> 01:22:26,118
You can't blame these men. Naturally
they are concerned. - Yes.

739
01:22:40,198 --> 01:22:45,800
Forgive us. We have
been cruel and unjust...

740
01:22:46,319 --> 01:22:50,920
...we have stolen,
tortured, killed.

741
01:22:51,560 --> 01:22:56,000
We will not, can not
resist you any longer.

742
01:22:57,319 --> 01:23:01,359
The Prophet (peace and
blessings be upon him ) said:

743
01:23:02,359 --> 01:23:06,680
'' There will be no
executions, no purchase.

744
01:23:07,158 --> 01:23:10,760
Mecca will be healed
by the spirit of Islam.

745
01:23:10,920 --> 01:23:16,479
l am certain it will. And
i too must witness...

746
01:23:16,680 --> 01:23:20,880
...that there is
no god but God.

747
01:23:21,158 --> 01:23:26,238
And that you Muhammad,
are his Prophet.

748
01:23:28,720 --> 01:23:31,399
l'll prepare the city.

749
01:23:33,479 --> 01:23:38,560
l am glad that despite
my best efforts l can say...

750
01:23:38,680 --> 01:23:42,520
...''Muhammad lives''.

751
01:23:48,640 --> 01:23:53,078
From rulers to the
simple robes of Islam...

752
01:23:56,038 --> 01:23:59,279
...may it always be so.

753
01:25:03,399 --> 01:25:08,720
You are free forever now my
friend, with body and soul.

754
01:25:26,880 --> 01:25:31,359
Home at last.
- Thanks to God.

755
01:25:52,439 --> 01:25:55,520
l'll never forget
the feeling of that day.

756
01:25:55,760 --> 01:25:59,399
lt was filled with
indescribable joy.

757
01:25:59,520 --> 01:26:03,319
A few years later in Medina
after a short illness...

758
01:26:04,038 --> 01:26:09,600
...The Prophet (peace and
blessings be upon him ) died.

759
01:26:10,359 --> 01:26:15,920
He was 63. He always lived
a simple and humble life...

760
01:26:16,078 --> 01:26:19,118
...giving everything
he had to the poor.

761
01:26:20,439 --> 01:26:24,800
l wish l had met The Prophet.
l wish l had heard him speak.

762
01:26:25,158 --> 01:26:29,600
Yes. But the words
of God live on.

763
01:26:29,720 --> 01:26:33,920
Where will you go now?
- l don't know.

764
01:26:34,038 --> 01:26:38,038
l know. Maybe you can stay
here and work in Mecca.

765
01:26:38,158 --> 01:26:41,038
What kind of
working you do?

766
01:26:41,960 --> 01:26:45,880
lt's beautiful.
- l used to have a loom like yours...

767
01:26:46,000 --> 01:26:50,600
...but l lost it,
l lost everything.

768
01:26:51,840 --> 01:26:55,760
lf he had some wool, he could
use our loom don't you think?

769
01:26:55,880 --> 01:26:58,479
Yes, yes he could.

770
01:26:59,399 --> 01:27:06,359
Sir, you could have Bashu's wool.
- No, it belongs to you.

771
01:27:06,600 --> 01:27:09,960
No it belongs to you now.

772
01:27:13,600 --> 01:27:17,920
Come on, we'll take him
to the market together.

